</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=usildordhujata>Usildor Dhujata</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Crypt Pimp</span><br>  Posts: 1257<br> <font color=#330000>(11/17/03 5:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1140.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/poeticsarcasm/images/marblemn.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NOZ !</span><hr size=1> Ok Ram it went over your head.  Maybe I said it wrong.  Let me break it down a bit better.  You seem to think that I am saying that they should have known this was going to happen 3 years ago or whenever sleeper was first written.  NO.  I am not saying this.  So please. drop that argument.  What I AM saying is that SINCE then, changes have been made to the game.  Now...when sleeper was first written, it was set up to have a certain number of HP's and a certain amount of regen, and given the amount of DPS possible by a large zerg force AT THE TIME, the sleeper was for all intents and purposes impossible.  I agree with you there.  BUT.  The DPS possible and the skills available have been changed by SOE since then.  So now, it is VERY possible to kill sleeper (obviously now) with the changes they made to the game.  They SHOULD, if they wanted it to truly be IMPOSSIBLE, made it so that it was.  <br>
<br>
Since they didnt change the sleeper to accomodate the DPS and abilities of the current EQ, only two assumptions can be made:  1)  They don't want it to be impossible anymore or 2) They just forgot to even look at it.<br>
<br>
Now, if it's number one, then the script should have been changed.  If it's two, it's still a fuck up.  I'm sorry but if your'e going to market a product, especially expansions of a previous product, then yes..you should and ARE responsible for anything you fail to update of the previous versions.  Now, I can somewhat understand them missing it, the game afterall is very complex.  But my problem is that there have been times when parts of the game certainly werent finished and purposely sabotaged, which you know damn well have happened.  I personally fail to see how they could miss the fact that they needed to update the sleeper since it's the only &quot;impossible&quot; mob they designed (even though that term obviously doesnt apply).  But if they did, fine.  But it's still half-assed.  And I dont buy the fact that it was a script error when everything in the zone reset, not just sleeper.  But whatever.  You say its unfair for a company to be expected to update their own product they are expanding.  I say its unfair to the consumer to do anything else.  And shipping products that arent updated and in some cases, unfinished, is just shitty in general.  <br>
<br>
And in terms of your analogy, it'd be like if your company made a new version of the particular product and then failed to have you update your software.  All of a sudden, it doesnt work anymore but that's just a normal software scenario?  Nope, sorry.  I can understand.  But this isn't something SoE is giving us out of the kindness of their hearts.  This is a service they make a fucking shit load of money on.  This is a product we pay for and while bugs are expected, unfishied...sabotaged...or major non-updated content is not just part of the game.  Blizzard sure doesnt seem to have these sort of problems.  I dont expect perfect.  But I expect reasonable. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
