<br>
Even if our little baby-guild took Vindi down and EVEN IF I got the last shot in and EVEN IF I was lucky enough to get the BP, I STILL wouldn't get some twisted satisfaction about being the last one to hit him.  To tell you the truth, I almost never even look.<br>
<br>
As you know, I seem to MT more often than not when we raid (and I go).  As a matter of a fact, for a while, I was sometimes the ONLY melee there, so having the last hit was pretty much a given.  All the same ... take the clerics out and I am probably not going to live long enough to land a third hit, much less a last one.  I have seen some people mention it, sure ... it is funny when a chanter drops a mob with a dagger stab for 7.  I do get a laugh when my necro whaps a mob for 15 dmg and kills it.  Sure, it's funny, but unless I am soloing, I see it as pretty damn cheap to claim some badge of honor becasue you &quot;hit it last&quot;.  But like I said ... maybe it's just me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tryphyna>Tryphyna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 220<br> <font color=#330000>(11/18/03 9:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1140.topic&index=60>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.angelfire.com/games5/tryphyna/images/gothav1.gif HEIGHT=131 WIDTH=67></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: m</span><hr size=1> I agree with you Tibult, with two exceptions.<br>
